Text: This past week has been limited in technical progress.
I had underestimated the level of planning which needs to go into the project.
It took a lot longer than expected to tease out the details.

This was frustrating for myself and I believe that we should have planned better in weeks where it was questionable where the direction of the project was going and we should have been more decisive during that time.
I find my technical skills to be significantly lacking in simple activities like downloading programmes needed and being able to follow online instructions to learn new tech.

With that being said I find online tutorials on YouTube to be helpful alongside peer to peer teaching being very helpful which will help me overcome these challenges should I face them in the next week.
I am fortunate to have people on the team with more advanced technical experience to ease the learning curve for myself.
I feel frustrated however as I would like to gather more traction with advancing my technical skills.
This next will I will overcome this by moving forward quickly and allocating my time wisely regarding the learning resources I plan to use.
I am foreseeing an issue being time pressure as we have the bulk of our technical work to achieve in the next week as well as interviewing to extract information from our clients.
Another thing to consider this next week is that we have a lot of course deadlines due such as the presentation due in a week and the following Wednesday having the reflective report due.
I have learnt a lot about my strengths and am looking forward to working on the technical skills in areas where I'm not too strong.
I think I underestimated my ability to achieve the goals set out for the project due to my lack of knowledge in knowing what the direction of the project would take.
I am currently not on track to achieve these goals due the ambiguity in the beginning.
